“Notwithstanding the experiences of 2020, as citizens march into the new year, there should be a change of narrative for the nation in 2021,” he said. He urged Nigerians to strengthen their bond of unity in their collectively patriotic resolve to rescue the nation. “The PDP prays for our nation and urges all hands to be on the deck to ensure a happy and more peaceful 2021,” he said. The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has commended Nigerians for their resilience in standing up for the unity and survival of the nation in spite of the daunting challenges. The party gave the commendation in a statement issued by its National Publicity Secretary, Mr Kola Ologbondiyan on Monday in Abuja to commemorate the 59th… October 1, 2019 In "News" The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has urged Nigerians to step into 2019 with unwavering optimism, faith and hope of a new era of peace, national cohesion and economic prosperity. December 31, 2018 In "News" Speaker of the House of Representatives, Mr. Yakubu Dogara; political parties and umbrella platforms for churches, yesterday, urged Nigerians not to despair in the face of challenges in the New Year but work towards surmounting the multifaceted problems bedeviling the nation. January 1, 2018 In "News"